  <prompt>
    Implement type compatibility validation logic in FieldMappingService. Define the Strict mode
    compatibility matrix that determines which field type mappings are allowed. Block incompatible
    mappings with clear error messages.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer with expertise in TypeScript and data validation patterns.
    Understand Dataverse field types and their conversion compatibility.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Type compatibility validation implemented in FieldMappingService with Strict mode matrix.
    Incompatible mappings should be rejected with descriptive errors during admin configuration
    and at runtime.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Type compatibility ensures that field mappings make sense (e.g., you can map a Lookup to
      Text, but not Text to Lookup). Strict mode is the only mode for R1 - Resolve mode with
      automatic conversion is planned for a future release.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
