  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given a Lookup source type, when getCompatibleTargetTypes is called, then Lookup and Text
      are returned as compatible targets.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given a Text source type, when isTypeCompatible(Text, Lookup) is called, then false is
      returned (Text cannot map to Lookup in Strict mode).
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given a profile with an incompatible rule, when validateProfile is called, then an error
      is returned identifying the incompatible mapping.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All unit tests pass for type compatibility matrix.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Type compatibility matrix from CLAUDE.md:
    - Lookup: [Lookup, Text]
    - Text: [Text, Memo]
    - Memo: [Text, Memo]
    - OptionSet: [OptionSet, Text]
    - Number: [Number, Text]
    - DateTime: [DateTime, Text]
    - Boolean: [Boolean, Text]

    Key principle: You can always "widen" to Text, but never "narrow" from Text.
  </notes>

